== English == 
=== Etymology===
Humorous formation from [[dyslexia]] by metathesis as if due to dyslexia.

=== Noun===
'''lysdexia''' ''(uncountable)''
# ''(humorously)'' [[Dyslexia]].
# Being prone to [[metathesis]] in reading,  writing, or speech due to (real or imagined) [[dyslexia]].

===Quotations===
* '''2003:''' Priase to Hodwy, Dog of '''Lysdexia'''. —Willow Polson, ''The Veil's Edge'' [http://print.google.com/print?id=_nsVcjo5Ey0C&pg=PR21&lpg=PR21&sig=G-XeHvu1zxjmbLAgMv4k2wwffbE]
* '''2005:''' “My apologies. My '''lysdexia''' must be kicking in again. What I meant to say was, ‘Who beath thou?’” —Stefan Koski, ''Miscellaneous Philosophy'' [http://print.google.com/print?id=Ib0t1Xy44rcC&pg=PA121&lpg=PA121&sig=6G0WLo7Xc0GNfgX7JeybR-T4SGo]

